Mobiles.LongDescription: `gAn innkeeper stares out into the air, unaware of his surroundings.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis human looks very relaxed as he leans against the marble desk, buta closer look tells of something amiss.  His eyes are dead and unresponsiveand his facial features totally lack any sign of interest of the worldaround him.  He is clad in a simple, but official-looking, tunic withmatching pants held up by a brown leather belt.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA boy sits by the hearth, galloping a wooden toy horse back and forth in the flickering light.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThe boy performs the monotonous task of making the toy horse gallop infront of the fire.  His hair is neatly combed, and his wide-set eyes stareunblinking into the wall.  Why is this boy here, all alone?  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gThe statue of a stone demon blocks a trapdoor with wings and claws.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA grim-looking statue sits hunched before an iron trapdoor that leadsinto the tower.  Its wings are stretched to their full spam, effectivelypreventing passage.  The menacing, toothy grimace is sure to make even themost battle-hardened knight to think twice before getting close to thispetrified monstrosity.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA man rotates a pig impaled on a spit over one of the cooking fires.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThe man is dressed like a farmer, and looks out of place in the busykitchen.  Given his sun-bleached hair and tanned face it is likely that heis from the village of Stillwater.  Sweat runs down his forehead, into hiseyes, but he gives no indication that it bothers him.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA red-haired man is works the winch here.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA half-naked man is working the winch, his sooty skin is striped fromperspiration as he is working the crank.  Every now and then he unloads thecontents of the winch basket, but mostly he just works tirelessly withoutshowing any emotion.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA girl is preparing a meal here, using her knife with exceptional skill.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA frail little girl that barely can see over the edge of the table, ishacking vegetables into neat squares here.  The only thing to cover her upis a stained white apron and a ribbon to keep the hair out of her eyes.  Herface has the same vacant expression as the villagers of Stillwater.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aThe baker stands by the counter, kneading dough.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThe baker almost looks like some kind of snowman, all covered in flourand specks of dough.  The sleeves of his white shirt are rolled up and hisapron is..  Flowered.  That apron is very conspicious in this somber place.He runs back and forth in the kitchen, off north to the ovens to put anotherbread in the oven and back to the pantry to get ingredients for his endlessbaking.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `dAn iron pipe flails madly here!``
Mobiles.Description: `cOne of the jointed iron pipes has come to life!  It is flailing madlyat you, trying to defend the machine that it is attached to.  Sparks fly asthe iron tentacle hits the stone floor as it whips at you!  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA kitten chases a mouse around a pile of plates.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA fluffy kitten scampers around the room, chasing mice it only stopsmomentarily to paw some piece of food that at falled cast 'haste' falled tothe floor.  It is covered in both soot and flour,leaving a black and whitetrail behind.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA mouse tries to stay away from stomping feet and pouncing cats here.``
Mobiles.Description: `cDarting left and right, the mouse avoids getting squashed by humanfeet, not to mention the kitten that seems to think that this rodent is avery funny toy.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `oBlixfog`h stands here, drawing mystical patterns in the air.``
Mobiles.Description: `cDressed in white robes and some big round spectacles, this man smilesbrightly, seemingly at nothing.  Carrying a wand in one hand and acolor-changing crayon in the other, he paints both magical patterns in theair and ordinary, child-like, pictures on the 'walls' of thistwo-dimensional space.  Glittering gadgets can be seen in the wide sleevesof his robes.  His innocent blue eyes scan the surroundings for a free spaceto draw something on and suddenly he kneels down to play with afunny-looking Vro'ath doll.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA ghostly librarian glides back and forth between the bookshelves.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA translucent and withered old lady floats around among thebookshelves, wearing only tattered rags to cover her fragile form.  Fromtime to time she mutters something and relocates some old volume.  Strangelyenough this ghost wears a green little bow in her hair, a bow that istangiable unlike the rest of her garb.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aAn enraged ghost floats around, searching for intruders.``
Mobiles.Description: `cSomething must have upset this ghost librarian, though librarians are avicious breed, this one wields the powers of the underworld.  It is flyingaround between the different rooms of the library, searching for life formsthat have guts to tear out.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA moldy old skeleton sits by the desk, scribbling on a parchment, unaware of his lack of... life.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis scholar seems to have been working non-stop for several centuries,a never-ending chore of reading through books, perusing maps and writenotifications on pieces of parchment.  He did not even stop after the fleshand muscles of his body were long gone and his clothes had rotted away fromhis yellowed bones.  Blotches of ink has colored what is left of his handsblack, a thick stone ring rattles on his right hand's middle finger.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aOddus the book binder sits hunched over a damaged book.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis muscular man would fit better as a blacksmith than being a bookbinder.  With immense concentration he hunches over a damaged leather volumeon the floor, applying a new blue leather binding with golden letters alongthe spine.  Clad in the same rural clothes as many of the villagers ofStillwater, this man seems out of place this far down from the surfaceworld.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA phantom delegate is absorbed in discussion with the other ghosts.``
Mobiles.Description: `cCompletely translucent this delegate hoovers a an inch over its chair,spitting in fury over some current argument with the other ghosts.  Books,chairs and other things that might hurt a not-dead person flies across theroom (not to mention through the ghosts they were aimed at).  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aGrowling like a dog another phantom delegate has risen from its chair.``
Mobiles.Description: `cCompletely translucent this delegate hoovers a an inch over its chair,spitting in fury over some current argument with the other ghosts.  Books,chairs and other things that might hurt a not-dead person flies across theroom (not to mention through the ghosts they were aimed at).  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aDrooling prufusely a phantom delegate sleeps in its chair.``
Mobiles.Description: `cCompletely translucent this delegate hoovers a an inch over its chair,spitting in fury over some current argument with the other ghosts.  Books,chairs and other things that might hurt a not-dead person flies across theroom (not to mention through the ghosts they were aimed at).  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aBooks and papers fly as this phantom delegate throws a fit.``
Mobiles.Description: `cCompletely translucent this delegate hoovers a an inch over its chair,spitting in fury over some current argument with the other ghosts.  Books,chairs and other things that might hurt a not-dead person flies across theroom (not to mention through the ghosts they were aimed at).  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `iKing Kingston sits here on his gold and diamond encrusted throne.``
Mobiles.Description: `hKing Kingston sits here on his gold and diamond encrusted throne.  Heappears to be a kind middle-aged man.  Too old to ride out to battle but notold enough to be someone's grandfather.  He has beautiful, blond hair likehis daughter and sparkling green eyes.  He wears robes of the finest silksand suedes.  All of his clothing is a rich royal purple with gold trim.  Hiscrown is gold with dark blue and purple stones befitting his station.  Healso wears the royal ring that matches the crown's color and design.  Hisroyal sword is of the finest craftsmanship.  It has words engraved upon itin an ancient tongue that has been long forgotten.  The handle of the swordis part gold and part purple.  When the King smiles, his face is said tolight up the entire room.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `iZephyrus, the dragon, stands guard proudly in front of the tower.``
Mobiles.Description: `hZephyrus, the dragon, stands here guarding the tower.  Parts of himsparkle in the sunlight like the deepest blood red rubies.  His skin looksdull enough to the unknowing eye but upon closer inspection, his scales areextremely intricate.  His eyes are set back into his forehead more than theusual dragon.  He appears to have been in a fight with some brave knight.No doubt THAT knight made a delicious snack.  His eyes are like bright bluesapphires and his teeth are like sharp white pearls.  His beauty gives offthe sense of safety in his presence.  The fire and smoke coming from hisnose and mouth however, warn people of the danger of getting involved withthis dragon.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `iPrincess Daffodil lies on the bed awaiting her savior.``
Mobiles.Description: `hPrincess Daffodil rests here on the bed next to the window.  She lieson a bed of sumptuous pillows made of the best satins and silks.  She isvery innocent looking.  She has blond hair the color of a field of wheat andsparkling emerald green eyes.  She is a classically beautiful princess.  Shewears a fancy pink satin dress lined with diamond studs.  Her delicate feetare encased in equally pretty pink satin shoes with diamond studded bows.Her crown is made of silver with pink stones that glint in the sunlight.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `dA small elderly woman rocks back and forth in her chair.``
Mobiles.Description: `hAn elderly woman sits in her chair rocking back and forth.  Back andforth.  There is a far away look in her eyes that makes anyone that sees herwant to give her a hug.  She is dressed in a shabby grey dress made of wool.Her shoes are worn thin around the soles and one is missing a shoelace.Maybe if someone talks to her she will feel better.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA poltergeist is yanking books out of the bookshelves here.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA swirling gust of smoke is leaving a trail of devastation behind, apoltergeist is not a foe to be underestimated.  A spirit form left in thematerial plane because of an untamable rage of the soul of the diseased one.It leads is undead existance for one reason only, and that is to spreadchaos.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA small winged imp flutters around here, cackling with glee.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis creature's sole reason for living is serving bigger and strongerbeings, but also to cause endless mischivousness wherever it appears.  Impshave a terrible repertoir of magic available to them, but only if theirmaster allows the use of it, this particular imp does not seem to have anyother reason in life than to flutter around on its bat wings and cackle.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA naked elf man is frantically banging his hands against the wall of the sphere.``
`aA man in a white coat rushes around in the laboratory, wearing holsters full of test tubes.``
Mobiles.Description: `cStanding only four feet tall, this little human is by no meansproportional, what he lacks in height, he makes up for in width.  Broaderthan he is tall he runs around in the laboratory, mixing chemicals in testtubes and handling the mind-boggling devices that are scattered around thelow-ceilinged hall.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aThe very epitome of obesity and intoxication sits here, drinking from different test tubes.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA naked blob of flesh sits here, chained to the wall.  The chain, atthis point, is merely a symbolic sign of imprisonment, this mountain ofhuman fat and skin would be hard pressed to move even an inch in anydirection.  His chins and chest are miscolored and blistered from spillingliquids that he has been forced to consume.  The shear mass of "Lardy"blocks any passage to the east.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA lean woman dusts the bottles here.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA woman in dirty robes cleans the glass jars and bottles upon theshelves, moving tirelessly and without showing any reaction to thesurroundings.  Her stare is blank and focused somewhere beyond this eerilylit chamber.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA canthi mage creates multicolored pills out of thin air here.``
Mobiles.Description: `cGleaming green eyes sparkles with amusement as this canthi male createspills out of thin air, just to make them disappear into a little white clothpouch hanging from his belt.  The mage's black hair tints slightly towardgreen and his skin is a sickly pale grey, contrasting his bright yellowrobes.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA crooked man leans over a stone sacrophagus, chanting in a coarse voice.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis man sweats profusely as he chants a sordid chant over the stonesarcophagus.  His words echoing through the room, getting a new meaning eachtime they bounce off a surface.  His once white robe is stained with clottedblotches of blood and a wickedly curved saw hanging from a strap around hiswrist.  A triumphant grin wrinkles his face as the chant nears itsconclusion...  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA terrible construct of human bodyparts staggers around, looking lost.``
Mobiles.Description: `cCreated by stitched-together bodyparts of different humans, thisabomination rolls his eyes frantically, as if not knowing it had broughtback to life.  Muscles and bones are visible through the pale and partlytranslucent skin that is stretched to a thin membrane over the monstersbody.  Guttural sounds crawls out of its parted, dry lips, terrible voice ofloneliness.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA man with a dark complexion weaves shadows into matter.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis bald man stands by the western wall, watching his shadow move overthe wall as he sweeps his long, green, velvet cape.  His brow is wrinkledwith concentration and his low-pitched voice resonates through theoctagonally shaped room.  Faded tattoos depicting outlandish circles andspirals cling to his skin like some kind of vampiric vines.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA grey shadow claws at your face!``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis translucent and shapeshifting shadow has somehow come to life through powerful magic.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aRoaring fire shrouds this terrible fire dragon!``
Mobiles.Description: `cAt the wave of a hand and a muttered word, the illusionist can make hisspectators' fantasies and fears come to life.  Wearing nothing but aneyeball charm around his neck and and illusionary garb, he practices hiscraft in solitude.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aThe beard of this mithril-clad dwarf is white with frost.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThe dearf's bearded face is a mask of stern, iron-willed, concentrationas he reads from a book placed on a lectern in front of him.  Theelementalist's hands move slowly in agile intricate movements that leavespatterns of white light in their wake.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aThe necromancer stands calmly by the pentagram, observing you.``
Mobiles.Description: `cBy the edge of the pentagram a golden-haired elf stands, his otherwiseperfect skin is spotted with fleshy sores, something very rare, if notunheard of, for an elf.  He is shrouded in flowing black robes that seems tobe a part of the surrounding darkness.  Irregular scars run up the insidesof his bare arms, perhaps battle scars or maybe they are self-inflicted.Stories tell about necromancers, and none of them describe the dark mages assane.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aThe enchanter stands here with one wand in each hand and several more in his belt.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA grinning canthi stands here, her grey-green skin gleaming in thelight of the single oil lamp.  She is merely clad in a black tunic and alaquered red leather belt.  Her shapely calves draws attention to herslender feet with webbed toes.  Her gills open and close with subtle suckingsounds as her marine-blue eyes wander over the ornate wand in her hands.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aAn ugly gnome sits cross-legged in the middle of the room, muttering.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA wrinkled, and very ugly, little gnome stands here, seeminglyoblivious to his lack of clothes.  Teeth necklaces and numerous charms hangin a leather thong around his stick-like neck, and blackened blood formpatterns all over his face and chest, most likely imbued with protectivespells.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA blob of warty green skin flails its tentacles around, trying to grab you!``
Mobiles.Description: `cYellow pus oozes out of this formless blob, stinking the room up realgood.  Tentacles flail around, trying to rape you as if you were a girl inan anime.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA giant man made out of quartz patrols the corridors here.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA man made of living quartz lumbers along on eternal patrol in thesilent corridors.  Its angular face displays nothing but a grotesque toothymouth.  A mouth that covers almost all of the front of its head.  One of thethree-fingered hands of the golem could easily palm the head ofa vro'athand, no doubt, crush it soon afterwards.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA man in grey and black clothes is bleeding to death here.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThe big assortment of daggers and metal tools that hang from this man'sbelt makes it safe to assume that he is a burglar or a thief, though not avery successful one, judging from his current, very mutilated, state.  Awhite hand is embroidered on the sleeve of his leather tunic.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA monk listens intently after something here...``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis man is the epitome of physical perfection, muscles play under hisolive skin and his handsome face is angular and shows a bit of boyishinnocence.  But his eyes wander aimlessly, each in a different direction,following the movements of the phantasms of his mind.  Occasionally buryinghis face in his hands, letting out a muffled cry of a helplessness.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA skeleton stands here, waiting until its needed.``
Mobiles.Description: `cLoose ashen skin hangs off the twisted skeletal frame of this guard.Its equipment and clothes makes it apparent that the mockery of lifetrudging along here was once an adventurer.  A rusted chainmail that couldfit several of the skeletons kind inside provides a meager protection.  Theundead's jawbone moves constantly as it mumbles and groans, cursing the magethat put it into this dreadful state.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA skeleton clad in adventurer's garb trudges along here.
Mobiles.Description: `cLoose ashen skin hangs off the twisted skeletal frame of this guard.Its equipment and clothes makes it apparent that the mockery of lifetrudging along here was once an adventurer.  A rusted chainmail that couldfit several of the skeletons kind inside provides a meager protection.  Theundead's jawbone moves constantly as it mumbles and groans, cursing the magethat put it into this dreadful state.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA skeleton clad in adventurer's garb trudges along here.
Mobiles.Description: `cLoose ashen skin hangs off the twisted skeletal frame of this guard.Its equipment and clothes makes it apparent that the mockery of lifetrudging along here was once an adventurer.  A rusted chainmail that couldfit several of the skeletons kind inside provides a meager protection.  Theundead's jawbone moves constantly as it mumbles and groans, cursing the magethat put it into this dreadful state.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA man is slowly withering away from old age.``
Mobiles.Description: `cAn old human leans against a corner for support.  Each gasping, drybreath seems to sock a little more life out of him.  His wrinkled andsagging face smiles at you weakly, he seems to be happy not having to diealone.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA hand is sticking out through the bars of a cell door waves you closer.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA hand sticks out between the bars of the cell door.  It looks strong,and remarkably clean in this foul dungeon.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA proud, silver-haired man stands here, eyeing you with his piercing gaze.``
Mobiles.Description: `cJudging from his long silver beard, this man seems to have beenimprisoned here for a very long time.  But some how he has managed to keepboth his shape and sanity.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aThis elven girl smiles at you, her blue eyes open with innocence.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis elven girl skips around happily, giggling and winking at everyoneshe meets.  She wears a plain leaf-green dress that is adorned with deep-redberries that matches her flushed cheeks.  Her wavy hair is tied into a shortpony-tail that bobs up and down as she moves.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aThe former court magician Efraim Otraphius stands here, looking down at you.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis is Efraim Otraphius, the revered court magician of Castle Dunlace,stories say that he long ago found the secret to eternal an eternal life.It is told that he once defeated Anouen Forudal in a magical duel, and fromthat day on he searched the realms for someone that could give him achallenge.  He found Carnifex, and now he is trapped in this this dungeon.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA growling vro'ath berserker charges into you!``
Mobiles.Description: `cRed-tinted skin, rolling eyes and a really, REALLY, big four-headedflail is all you see before this berserker warrior slams into you.  Awhimpering sound is heard from its throat, as if it was worrying it couldnot kill you fast enough, to move on to killing more people.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aAn undead minotaur howls stomps in fury as yet another challenger is before it.``
Mobiles.Description: `cAn large humanoid with the skeletal head of a bull charges around thepit here, attacking anything even remotely mobile.  Links of chainmail hangsfrom its jagged horns, testaments of ferocious, but probably shortencounters with enemies.  Each horn arched forward, jutting out from thebrown skull like two deadly scimitars.  Dried fur and rotting skin hang fromthe minotaurs thick skeletal frame, and even though this monster lacks anysubstance, apart from the bone, there is no doubt that it has no weaknesses.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA man clad in the now familiar garb of a thief of the hand, hides here.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis is Smidig, a thief that against all odds made it all the way downthrough the tower, unfortunately he ended up in a pit, and the only neighborwas an insane undead minotaur.  So he spends all day running away, it isonly a matter of time until he is killed.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA lich soldier handles a big halberd here, as if it was weightless.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA lich soldier trains tirelessly among his likes, it handles heavyweapons as if they were made of air, it dodges swings easily, even thoughit's clad in heavy scale armor.  A sickening aura of death surrounds thisunliving vro'ath.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA kalian practices with his daggers here, moving from shadow to shadow.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA kalian soldier practices with his deadly daggers here, he uses apurely offensive fighting style, that would only make sense to a being thatcould withstand huge amounts of physical punishment, as well as regeneratelost limbs within minutes.  His black cape flutters and suddenly he thereare two of him, his illusion fighting along his side, confusing the opponentutterly.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aCommander Ktraj stands here, surveying his soldiers' training.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThe training commander stands here with a stern look on his face.  Hestudies his soldiers' moves and now and then he shouts out an order.  Ktrajis a swordsman from the wastelands of Nowhere, his exploits are widely knownthroughout the world, how he ended up here.  Nobody knows, but who dares toquestion a man of his fighting provess?  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA villager of Stillwater is chained to the floor here, acting as a living practice dummy.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis villager pulls on his chains as he dodges incoming blows from thesoldiers practices, using him as a living dummy.  His eyes are teary withpanic and his forehead shiny with sweat.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA lich guard patrols in the shadow of the gate here.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA lich clad in dark robes patrols here with his cumbersome towershield, he trudges back and forth with only one purpose: to guard the gate.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA short skeleton clad in heavy armor sits on a bench here, twiddling its skeletal thumbs.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis is a pitiful little skeleton, formerly a gnome or some othernot-so-tall humanoid, the armor it is wearing is much too big, but does notseem to bother it.  A lance is leaning against a wall nearby, which seemsway too big for this diminutive skeleton to wield.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA villager works below the winch here, loading and unloading foodstuffs in and out of the basket.``
Mobiles.Description: `cWearing only a loin-cloth, this nearly-nude human works under the winchthat regularly disappears up into the tunnel leading straight up to thekitchen of the tower.  He put vegetables, fish, meat and other ingredientsinto the baskets in never-ending labor.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA necromancer oversees the slaves' work here, a menacing whip in hand.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA permanent grin stretches across the width of this lich's dreadfulskull, and inside of the eye sockets, dry, shrunken eyeballs rattle.  Hissilken robes are black, adorned with golden spiral patterns along the hem.His skeletal fingers curl around the handle of a fearsome two-tailed whipand in the other a glowing red orb.  He whips all slaves that walk tooclose, walk to slow, or that are just close enough for him to walk over andgive them a nasty "ka-pisch!"  Across the back.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA vro'ath slave carries a heavy wooden beam on his back.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA muscled vro'ath is here, dragging, lifting and carrying heavy objectsaround, things that would take two human slaves to move.  His face is a maskof self-loathing, to think that one of the slaver race would become theenslaved.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA tall elf with wearing nothing but a loin-cloth and angry red tattoos is here.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis necromancer is almost completely naked, devilish patterns adornhis pale skin, snaking between green and brown boils.  His eyes are fanatic,staring into space and his fingers absentmindedly scratch crusts and sores.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA cavalry rider leans back against the gate.``
Mobiles.Description: `cEyes glow white against his black skin, this cavalry rider is dressedcompletely in black leather adorded with silver studs.  He has a lean build,but in the sure way he moves, one can tell that there is nothing frail abouthim.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA skeletal horse rears, black hooves slashing through the air.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis is a living skeleton of a horse, not too comfortable to sit onwithout a saddle, but it never tires and it runs faster than the wind.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA dwarven engineer stands here, surveying the work on the catapult.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThe engineer in charge of the construction of the catapult, he ordersthe slaves around with hoarse barked commands.  His spectacled eyes do notmiss a detail, and every time a slave does something wrong, the engineer isfast to correct them.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA zombie dressed in a gleaming chainmail lumbers around here, muttering something about 'brains'.``
Mobiles.Description: `cNot really knowing what it does here, this zombie stands in the cavern,looking around for some spare brains to eat.  This is the perfect meatshield at the very front of an army, it does not care much about lost limbsas long as it gets to eat living flesh.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aGasping its last breaths, a slave lies dying here, ignored by everyone.``
Mobiles.Description: `cDriven past the point of normal exhaustion this slave's body is simplygiving up, not able to handle all the work without any food.  Crying indesperation this slave knows what will happen when it dies, it will bebrought back to this world, but as a mindless zombie.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA busy slave scurries down the cavern path, carrying packages.``
Mobiles.Description: `cSwaeting profusely, this slave runs down the path with heavy footfalls.It carries heavy packages wrapped in rough sack-cloth, and the scrunchednose of the slave indicates that whatever is in those packages, might notsmell that nice.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aDeformed by necromancy, Carnifex is here, waiting for your arrival.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis is Carnifex, once a normal human seeking rank and power in some armyof a forgotten age.  Realizing that his ambition was too big for a normalhuman's short life-span, he began to study the dark art of necromancy.  Butbeing a necromancer takes its toll.  Carnifex's body was forever changedfrom the enormous amounts of negative energy flowing through it.  It waschanged to something not quite undead, but not quite alive either...  Hisface was forever twisted into a grimace of smoldering pain, his skin stillintact and full of life, but instead of eyes, two dark holes bore into hisskull behind his eyelids.  Hellish green whisps of flame escape his mouth ashe breathes through his lips.  Bits of bone protrude from his otherwiseflawless white skin, sticking out of him from wounds that will never heal.The skin and muscle on his right arm seem to have been ripped off, exposingthe white bone underneath.`cThe horrible visage that is Carnifex strides back and forth but stopssuddenly as he detects your presence...  His bleeding lips stretch in agruesome grin.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA baker automatically rolls out the dough of some kind of bread here.``
Mobiles.Description: `cHis arms are white with flour and his face is sweaty from working nearthe ovens.  He wears a white apron thats tied around his neck and waist.His stare is empty as he is performing his duties without faltering.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA giant lich stands here, wielding a blood-red reaver blade.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThe man standing before you looks as though he had just a crawled outfrom his grave.  Whats left of his pale white skin almost glows with a darklight that seems to fill the room.  Bleached bones protrude in places andcan easily be seen through what does remain of his skin.  His gray hairlooks as though it was made from spider's silk and is almost ready to fallfrom his dried scalp.  His arms are folded across his chest in completeconfidence.`cHis sword reeks with the stench of death at his side, always ready toreap another soul from the poor fools who come to chalenge him.  He turnshis head and looks at you as though he just noticed you.  Looking within hisempty eye sockets you see cold darkness stretching infinately within him.It chills your heart as his evilness seems to spark like wildfire about him.He grins as he looks you up and down revealing rotten decayed teeth.  Andyou begin to wonder what kind of hell could spawn such a being.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aAn undead vro'ath stands here, guarding the iron bar door to the north.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThe stupid, rotting, expression on this zombie's face tells of manyhours of just standing around, at this very spot, guarding a gate that cannot be opened from the inside from non-existant enemies inside a big coplexof his undead companions.  Formerly a vro'ath, this zombie has a huge bulk,and the scars on his face tells of his formerly low rank, though it wasprobably more glamorous than his current one.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aYou pick out the panicky face of a human in the crowd of slaves.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThis human is shoved and pushed around as the crowd of slaves movearound him.  His face shows obvious signs of panic, and he rushes towardsyou as soon as you open the gate and enter the slave pens.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA vro'ath slave sits here, snarling at other slaves that get too close.``
Mobiles.Description: `cThe vro'ath sitting here growls and grumbles, clearly not suited to beenslaved.  He snarls at anyone getting too close to his place in the slavepen.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA tired-looking elf rests here, protecting her child.``
Mobiles.Description: `cAn elvish mother sits here, holding her baby in her arms, protecting itfrom the other slaves.  Her head nods sleepily, apparently she has beenprotecting her baby ever since it was born, and she is now nearing herlimit...  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aOne of the elite lich soldiers is here, inspecting the troops.``
Mobiles.Description: `cClad in the finest mithril armor, complete with weapons in leathersheats adorned with gold thread, this lich soldier inspects the troops.  Itis one of the elite soldiers, the finest warriors in Carnifex's undead army.Its bones are tightly wrapped in black silk, almost giving the lich's armsthe same thickness as that of a human's.  ``

Mobiles.ShortDescription: A captain of the undead army
Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA kalian sits by the fire, sucking the last remains of life from a squealing rat.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA kalian, by the rank of captain sits by the fire here, leaningleasiurely against a log.  His eyes are completely black except for theiris, which is dark green.  His grey skin borders on black and stretchessoftly over his handsome features.  He is clad in the finest mithril chain,paper thin and very flexible.  A odd, small, spiked ball hangs on a chainaround his neck.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: (no long description)
`dA featureless statue leans against the wall here.``
`aA hamster is here, it looks confused.``
`hA pale man walks around here, groaning and moaning.``
Mobiles.Description: `aThis man seems to be half ghost, half zombie.  He shuffles around theshed without any apparent sign of goal.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `i*`kAn animated pumpkin head is jumping around here, cackling evilly`i*``
Mobiles.Description: `iAiiee! It is a living pumpkin! Kill or run!``

Rooms.TpMsg: You notice a hidden village below the hill!
Rooms.ExitMsg: `dThe grass rustles as`h $n`d wades out of sight.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `dWaist-high brown grass sway in the wind all around you, making it looklike the ground is moving.  Trailing the sloping hill to the south you spota weather-beaten windmill, catching the wind from the wast ocean.  Below thewindmill a small village sprawls around some kind of tree.  Behind you thesmall pier bravely stretches out into the waters, but the lack of boatsconfound you, how would an apparent fishing village survive without boats?`dA ancient granite pillar rises from the grass.``

`dYou stand at the base of the hill, and a small path widens into a roadfarther ahead.  The path does not look like it has been used in a long time,though the crusted earth has withstood the spread of vegetation a brokenwagon wheel and a broken bottle lying in the middle of the path is atestament of how seldom people climb the hill.  ``

`dThe village shows no sign of life from the outside, if it was not forthe neatly kept street and the intact windows, one might think that this wasa ghost town.  The wind in your back brings the scent of the sea to yournostrils, but when you breathe in you sense the smell of freshly bakedbread.`d`d  A rickety shed is to the east, seemingly a place to house a carriage, thougha carriage would do little good in this village on the edge of the world.``

Rooms.MaxMsg: `dThe shed is cramped as it is.``
Rooms.EnterMsg: `h$n`d squeezes into the already cramped shed.``
Rooms.ExitMsg: `h$n`d goes out through the big door.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `dA dusty room, but yet neatly kept.  Halters, saddles and various toolsfor rapairing wheels hang on the walls and lie on benches by the thin boardwalls.  Almost all of the west wall consists of a large double-door.  Narrowopenings just under the ceiling lets in rays of light that illuminates someswirling dust.  ``

`dThe well-kept cobblestone street stretches narrowly between a pair ofstone buildings.  White plastered structures reflect the sun's brilliantrays upon the street.  A criss-cross of dark brown, nearly black, woodenpanels frame the small windows and black iron balconies on the second floor.On the rail of each balcony planters with an abundancy of crimson redflowers can be seen.  And in the shade provided by the walls of thebuildings high-seated benches rise from a thin patch of grass.  You stillcannot see any villagers, nor any animals or birds in the sky, somethingseems out of place...  `````dTo the east a swinging `hsign`d proclaims the village's inn,perhaps you will find people in there?``

`dYou find yourself in a cramped room with a low ceiling.  Thewindow-less walls seem to lean inwards in an attempt to crush you.  Nopaintings adorn the walls, but the blue and yellow maze-patterned`h carpet`don the floor makes up for the lack of decor.  A ridiculously small marble`hdesk`d sits next to the great stairs.  So this is the inn.  You are notimpressed.  ``

Rooms.RoomName: The Sleeping Lamb Inn - Second Floor
Rooms.RoomDescription: `dThe white-painted walls has started to flake and bleached pantings hangin small square brass frames next to the doors that lead in all cardinaldirections except west.  A breeze finds its way in through the open balconyhatch from the quiet town outside.  ``

Rooms.MaxMsg: `dThere is only room for one person on the balcony.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `dThe air is much better out here on the balcony compared to the mustyold air inside the inn.  The wonderful smell of newly baked bread drifts inon the wind from the bakery, down the street to the south.  Across thestreet there is a house that looks completely deserted, the rooms that canbe seen through the windows are bare, but the door to the house is wideopen...  ``

`dThis is a simple room without any unnecessary embellishments, there isa chair, a narrow bed next to a small bedside table and a round window highup on the east wall.  Wooden beams criss-cross across the ceiling, givingthis room a feeling of rustic stability.  ``

`dThis house has been emptied of people, without a struggle though, foodhave been left on the plates on the dinner table, the axe still hangs on itshook next to the firewood next to the hearth.  Why would a whole family justleave their home like this and not even take anything with them?  ``

`dThe narrow streets widens into a square to the south on which a mightyoak casts its shade, a gently sloping alley squeezes its way between twotall buildings to the east, down towards a brown lake.  The cobblestones areworn by the feet of several generations of villagers visiting the bakery tothe west.  ``

`dStone walls reflects a pleasant warmth from the oven on the west wall.The wide oven, in which a dozen loaves of bread would easily fit, alsoradiates the flickering light of a roaring fire.  The air is thick with thefragrance of newly baked bread.  The bakery's wares lie enveloped oncheckered cloths on benches along all but the western wall.  Except thecrackling of the fire, the shop is quiet and peaceful.  ``

`dLacking the rats and refuse you would find in a city, this alley israther boring in comparision.  The walls on either side consist of anirregular mosaic of stones, fitting together as if cut from the very sameblock of granite.  Above, a pale sea sky can be seen, framed in by the`dshadowed edges of the roof-tops.``

`dA mighty oak spread its leafless branches above, its trunk disappearingdown into the ground through the cobblestones of the square, a square thatis, in fact, round.  Mystical iron patterns snake through the square in theshape of a five-pointed star.  Blood-red sap seeps out of recently madepuncture wounds in the tree's bark.  The holes almost look like the cryingeyes of some deformed and dying animal.  The oak twitches in response to thesuddenly chilling wind.  ``

`dUndented tables and benches are neatly places in rows along the southand north walls.  The straw on the floor looks fresh and there is not even astain of mead under the taps of the barrels behind the bar.  On every table,candles are placed on clean tablecloths.  This tavern has somehow evadedall signs that that costumers would leave behind.`d`dSomething about this village seems very wrong...``

`dThis bare room is poorly illuminated by the few remaining embers in thefireplace.  A large black stain is barely visible by the door, and on theopposite wall, two crumbled-up blankets lie.  Smashed furniture lie in aheap close by the hearth, the wood seems to have been used to feed thedwindling fire.  ``

`dThe cobblestones of the village have here given way to a stomped dirtpath that spirals around the hill, leading to the windmill.  A peaceful`dbrook separates this slope from the village of Stillwater overpassed by acompact log bridge.  The hillside is covered by purple heathers that havealmost overgrown the path to the top.  ``

`dThe wind is stronger up on the hill, accompanied by soft whooshingsounds a breeze propells the billowing sails of the windmill.  Bright yellowperennial flowers are planted in wooden buckets with black iron handles onthe sides of the windwill door.  To the south the hilly terrain soon turnsinto bare rock mountains.  And to the north, past the quaint village, rollsthe endless ocean.  ``

Rooms.RoomName: A Path Leading Out of the Village
Rooms.RoomDescription: `dThis path looks as though it should be busy with villagers, seeing asthe well is to the south and the lake where the villager's ought to washtheir clothes is down the cliff to the east.  ``

`dThis is the well, a small area of rock cleared of grass and soil and ahole boring down into the earth.  A lid has been put over the hole toprevent things, and people, from falling into the well.  There is a smallhatch that one can open to sink the nearby bucket to get water withouthaving to move the heavy lid itself.  ``

`dCliff on either side, this sandy slope leads down to the lake that liesserene within a barrier of grey cliffs.  Grass that has not been swept downthe slope pokes out of the white sand underneath.  ``

`dSharp flint rocks protrude from the sand like the giant fangs of someundeground monster, the sandy shore disappears down into the dark waters ofthe lake.  The lack of wind down here makes the air stink of deadvegetation.  ``

`dSharp flint rocks protrude from the sand like the giant fangs of someundeground monster, the sandy shore disappears down into the dark waters ofthe lake.  The lack of wind down here makes the air stink of deadvegetation.  ``

`cThe dark water is encapsuled on all sides by high cliffs, leaving it inshadows most of the day.  Kelp-like vegetation float around on the surfaceof the lake like small islands made of spongy green grass.  Far downunderwater several mysterious lights flicker, what is down there?  ``

`cThe dark water is encapsuled on all sides by high cliffs, leaving it inshadows most of the day.  Kelp-like vegetation float around on the surfaceof the lake like small islands made of spongy green grass.  Far downunderwater several mysterious lights flicker, what is down there?  ``

`cThe dark water is encapsuled on all sides by high cliffs, leaving it inshadows most of the day.  Kelp-like vegetation float around on the surfaceof the lake like small islands made of spongy green grass.  Far downunderwater several mysterious lights flicker, what is down there?  ``

`cThe dark water is encapsuled on all sides by high cliffs, leaving it inshadows most of the day.  Kelp-like vegetation float around on the surfaceof the lake like small islands made of spongy green grass.  Far downunderwater several mysterious lights flicker, what is down there?  ``

`dBrown grass whips angrily in the stiff ocean breeze, the endless seastretches out into the distance under the pale sky, and this peice of landseems to be inhabited as there is no sign of any roads.  But further up thehill there is some kind of ancient pillar erected.  ``

`dThe shore is rough and stony, little grows this close to the ocean.The salty smell of the ocean is thick in the air, and kelp and jellyfishhave been washed ashore.  Farther south a grassy hill protects will valleybeyond from the strong ocean breeze.  ``

`gA weather-worn stone tier stretches out into the grey ocean waves, thisis the only sign of nearby civilization, even though it is not much, itlooks more like a big rock than something man-made.  To the south there is agrassy hill preventing any insight to what is farther inland.  ``

```oThe world around you is a weightless darkness as you fall down the well.```````hThe gleam of light overhead is growing smaller and smaller.```````aAn echo catches your ear and you prepare for impact!``

`aFar down into the well, dark water, no way of getting out, perhaps this`awas not such a good idea after all...  The walls consis of slippery stone``that is impossible to get a good hold of...  Damn.  ``

`aThis seems to be the roof of a tower that has somehow sunk into thebedrock, the strange symbols engraved into the chiseled stones tell ofpowerful magic.  Recent visitors has left a trail in the rubble and dustthat cover the roof...  ``

`aThis seems to be the roof of a tower that has somehow sunk into thebedrock, the strange symbols engraved into the chiseled stones tell ofpowerful magic.  Recent visitors has left a trail in the rubble and dustthat cover the roof...  ``

`gThe smoky stairwell acts as a makeshift pantry, on every step of thespiraling stairs there are sacks, boxes and baskets containing variousingredients for food.  Nets of salted fish hang from rusted hook on thewalls.  A lone torch is flickering by the narrow doorway that leads to aroom that smells of cooking.  ``

Rooms.EnterMsg: `b$n navigates through the maze of food containers.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `gBarrels of salted meat and fish lines the walls, bottles of wine piledon top.  Shelves on the stone walls holds various jars of spices and driedvegetables.  Smoke swirls through holes just above the door that must leadto the kitchen and is sucked up through the stairwell.  An out-of placeweapon rack leans against a sack of flour.  ``

Rooms.EnterMsg: `b$n pants as $e walks into the hot kitchen.``
Rooms.ExitMsg: `bSweating profusely, $n leaves the kitchen in a hurry.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `gThe heat radiating from the ovens and cooking fires is breathtaking,and if the raging fires were not enough to blind one, the billowing smokedoes is.  Pots and pants hang from hooks on the wall and great bronzecauldrons are waiting in niches next to the ovens.  Malicious-looking toolsof food preparation can be found in the drawers under the cutting boards.

Rooms.EnterMsg: `b$n walks into the kitchen, eyeing the food on the table.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `gThis seems to be the part of the kitchen where the ingredients of themeals are prepared.  A long table seems to be the center of activity as thekitchen helpers shuffle around mechanically, its old and jagged and coveredwith all kinds of vegetables, meat, fish and mushrooms.  ``

`gJust a few feet off the edge of the balcony is a solid wall of granite,it seems like someone chiseled this cleft in the bedrock for the solepurpose of using the winch that crouches on the ledge of the platform likesome giant insect.  ``

Rooms.ExitMsg: `bLeaving footprints in the flour, $n walks off to the $T.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `gFootprints in the flour-dusted floors run all across the room in silenttestament of the amount of labor the kitchen seems to require to make endsmeet.  On the counter doughs, pies and of course a generous amount of flourcan be found, should the urge for baking amount.  ``

`gGreat tubs for washing dishes are full with porcelain plates, glassesand various spoons, forks and knives.  Things too fancy for the peopleliving on this floor of the tower.  The water is supplied by pipes thatsnakes along the roof from the west.  ``

Rooms.EnterMsg: `bGiving the machine a wary glance, $n walks into the room.``
Rooms.ExitMsg: `bMaking sure not to trip on any of the pipes, $n leaves.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `gIn the center of this is a strange monstrum of an apparatus, pipesleading out of it, through the floor, along the roof and snaking all overthe floor.  A glowing golden sphere pulses energy from inside the machinescore.  At drips cast 'create spring' from the the joints in the iron pipes,this must be the towers water supply.  The clanking, hissing and bubblingseems to intensity as your hand nears the hatch on the machines belly, thehatch covering that beautiful golden sphere...  ``

Rooms.ExitMsg: `b$n silently walks out of the room.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `gCompared to the rest of this floor, this is a quiet room.  But theclanking of the strange machine can still be felt though, a low andinconsistant thumping through the heavy door to the south.  This room smellsrather clean and the quiet creaking of the hammocks instills a feeling ofdrowsiness...  ``

`gCompared to the half-pantry stairwell, this is much nicer, though notby much.  On the outer wall childish paintings are hung, all of them seemsto be portaying a spectacled man with lightning comming out of his hands.On some of them he is standing on men in black robes with frowningexpressions on their faces.  ``

`gThe trail of childish paintings continues on the outer wall of thespiraling stairwell, all basically of the same theme as the earlierpictures.  But one picture stands out: a picture of a man holding his armout, as if to shake hands with someone.  In front of that particularpicture, a yellow mat with a big purple 'Welcome' is placed.  ``

`gThis must be the library, bookshelves can be seen in all directions aswell as several desks here and there, for studying the ancient tomes.  Withthe risk of fires someone has taken the precation to incase all torches inglass spheres.  All the books are neatly organized, the bookshelf behind thecouch on the east wall is marked 'Fiction'.  ``

`gBookshelves span from wall to wall in this carpeted room, blue, greenand red leather-bound books sit next to eachother in seemingly endless rowsof knowledge.  There are openings the the barrier of booshelves to the southand to the east, barely big enough for an average-sized human to getthrough.  There is a small sign hanging down from the ceiling.  ``

`hA room on a sheet of paper, missing all three dimensions but yettangiable in some in inexplicable way.  Chairs encircles a flat table withno legs.  The chest, painted with grey and brown crayons, that sits in theround corner casts a shadow on something that would have been called 'floor'in any other room.  ``

`gBoxes are stapled high here, mostly containing maps and journals.  Whatlooks like a door can be seen on the south wall, almost completely hiddenbehind a stack of crates.  There is a sweet smell of rot in the air, it ishard to sense where it originates from, but it must be somwhere close.  ``

`gA large desk sits by the eastern wall, cluttered with piles of papersand maps.  The room is a mess, stacks of books litters the floor, coveredwith cobwebs and dust as if not touched in centuries.  A few diplomas sit incrooked frames that have fallen to the tarnished mat.  ``

`gThe 'Fiction' shelf continues and hundreds of volumes of all kinds ofstories and fairytales.  There are a few high-backed armchairs sittingaround a round tabled with a few thin novels on it.  A few books on themiddle of the eastern bookshelf are especially conspicious.  ``

`gThis is a quiet, and private, reading room, and for those who know howto access it, it is the perfect place to rest.  A fire burns in the hearthand in front of it lie furs and pillows.  The crackling of the fire is anice contrast to the deafening silence in the rest of the library.  ``

`gYet another room with bookshelves in all directions, lit by a fewmagical torches in the corners, prompting the flutter of shadows that livein the darkened doorways.  A thick red carpet muffles all sounds into aquiet murmur.  A sign marked 'Invention' creaks in its chains.  ``

`gThere is a round table in this room, it has lots of books scattered allover it.  This must be be some kind of study chamber.  A plain metal caseseems to be attached to the center of the table, containing quills and aninkwell.  ``

`gDeeper into the library the bookshelves marked 'Medicine' can be found,full of musty old tomes.  Some of the tomes are marked with black skulls,others with yellow mushrooms or green leaves.  A chart hangs in front ofsome book on the south wall, a chart picturing different mushrooms.  On themiddle of the lush red carpet underneath is a glass case.  ``

`gAll the books in the previous rooms of this floor make this room seembare.  The dreary stone walls are sparingly covered by green tapestries withgolden patterns in the likeness of graveyards.  The floor is no longercovered by thick carpets, making every footstep echo.  ``

`gThe bend in the corridor continues to the north, off to the echoingstairwell where a hulking form looms.  On the south wall is an elf-sized oakdoor with a lone bookshelf accompanying it.  The shelf is empty except for afew tarnished books.  A brass sign on the door reads 'Book Binder'.  ``

`gScattered throughout the room lies papers of different thickness andcolors.  Chests are full of square pieces of leather of various colors, formaking binders of books.  A selection of tools like razors, rulers and a canof gold paint sits unceremoniously in a corner.  ``

`gNearing the stairwell one still cannot see who, or what, is standing infront of the stairwell at the end of the corridor.  Unlike inside thelibrary, the torches in this passage are not magical, in fact they arebarely burning at all.  As the light is dwindling, the walls seem to movecloser together.  ``

Rooms.MaxMsg: The magic of the winged imp stops you.
Rooms.RoomDescription: `gWithout any illumination in the stairwell, it looks like a dark holeburrowing into the granite.  Echoes of dripping water is heard from below,as if a great sea cavern was buried underneath.  Long forgotten rings forholding torches mark the void of the stairwell opening.  ``

`hOnce upon a time, there was a King.  He lived in the biggest palace inall the lands.  This palace has a grand hall with tapestries and lots ofgold all around.  King Kingston, despite his riches, was very sad.  Hisbeautiful daughter, Princess Daffodil, was kidnapped by the scariest, red,firebreathing dragon ever, Zephyrus.  The rumor is that Zephyrus took her tothe highest room in the tallest tower.  The tower is very high and very darkand mysterious.  ``

`hComing over the final hill, the view is spectacular.  There stands thebeautiful red dragon, Zephyrus.  His scales glitter like rubies in thetreasure room of the palace.  His eyes are cold blue sapphire stones.  Hisbeauty belies the danger.  The smoke coming from his nostrils curls abouthis head like the horns of a devil.  Behind the dragon stands the tallesttower enrobed in green, dark fog.  The princess can be seen leaning on herwindowsill staring off into the distance, awaiting the day someone will cometo save her.  Zephyrus is keeping a sharp eye out for anyone with thecourage to attempt the rescue.  ``

`hResidual heat fills this small room.  The dragon has been smote but theremnants of his terror filled reign will live on for years in this building.The fog around the tower has begun to disappate.  The only thing left to donow is save the lovely princess Daffodil.  Along the back wall there is aset of stone stairs that can only lead to one place.  The highest room.  Thedarkness at the top is quiet and deadly.  The sense that something has beenamiss is in the air.  There is light at the top of the staircase.  A littleraven sits in his cage at the foot of the stairs.  ``

Rooms.RoomName: `kThe Highest Room in the Tallest Tower``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `hAt long last the quest for the princess is over.  There she is, sittingon a bed of sumptuous pillows looking beautiful and innocent.  The journeyhome will be long but certainly not dangerous now that the dragon is dead.With the princess along, the trip should be pleasant as well.  The King issure to have the reward ready and waiting for his daughter's hero.  A kissfrom the princess ends this lovely tale.  And they both live happily everafter.  ``

`gAnother spiraling stair bores deeper into the underground tower, intoplaces unknown to the surface world, but inhabited by magical creatures andthe enslaved villagers of Stillwater, who could be behind all this?  Whatkind of a being has the power to make even the dead work for it?  It allremains to be seen.  ``

`gTo the east, running water, and the clinking of glass can be heard,sometimes interrupted by shouts and explosions.  But the door is thick, andthe bed in the room is deep and comfortable, one could still get somewell-deserved rest in this relatively quiet chamber.  ``

`gVials bubble over magical fires all around in this laboratory.  Liquidsof all colors and consistencies are available to anyone who would be braveenough to sample them.  All kinds of eye-tearing odors vaft through thislow-ceilinged room.  Over by the lengthy table a considerate amount ofcavities made by corrosive acids demonstrates the hazards of moving aroundtoo carelessly.  ``

`gFoul-smelling fumes emanate from assorted brass cauldrons and thickliquids belch as bubbles burst on the surfaces of what does not look veryedible at all.  Metal baskets hold ingredients for whatever nasty brews arein the making here, ingredients like eyes, squirming worms, finger nails andfurther pieces.  Framed charts hang on the wall, listing ingredients in someunknown language.  ``

`gTubes, glass pipes and vials slithers all across this room, boilingwith yellow and green liquids.  It the instruments seem to be there for thefinal concoction discharged through a funnel into a bone cylinder with a tapattached.  The smell is absolutely horrible smelling of sulphur, and a quietbubbling from the devices that surround the room is almost drowned in theechoes of explosions and screams comming from all around.  ``

`gThis room seem to exist for the purpose of testing the physical limitsof creatures.  A large crystal sphere has been placed on a podium engravedwith runes of summoning, runes that will magically transfer any human-sizedbeing into the confines of the sphere.  Marked levers stick up from thefloor, apparently they operate some of the tubes going into the glassprison.  ``

`gGlass vials sit on shelves all around, barrels filled withmulti-colored powders are stacked high, none of the contents of them seemvery edible, yet someone has been scooping out large amounts just to put itin an eating bowl.  ``

`gAnother stone corridor, not illuminated by torches, but by anoccasional glowing puddle of some glowing chemical liquids that dig smallholes in the floor.  The empty sound of dripping can be heard from somewherenearby.  Deformed rats crawling with flies and maggots, head dipped into agelatinous glob of...  Something that only a rat would consider food.  ``

`gFrom ugly half-rotted brown mat to ugly drab ceiling, flasks sits onshelves, labeled with yellowed notes and containing all kinds of livingthings, now dead, that could fit inside.  Glowing green orbs of light floatover each shelf, casting their cold light over this morbid collection offetuses, heads, rodents and organs.  ``
`gNothing but four walls, a floor and a ceiling in here.Not easy to get lost at all.``

`gA howling wind sweeps down through the passage, stinking of death anddecay as if death itself cast her breath through this place.  The remaininglit torches fight a losing battle against the gusts of wind and seem toemanate from the center of the corridor.  ``

`gSpherical pea-sized pills are sorted by color into an uncountableamount of urns, large as a dwarf down to small as a sidhes drinking pitcher.One of the urns, one of the larger, stands out.  A yellow barrel-shaped urncontaining copious amounts of sugar.  The square rug by a counter crackleswith the remains of multicolored pills.  ``
`gAcidic smoke has corroded the stones making out the floor, ceiling andwalls of this corridor.  Apparently someone has tested out some kind ofdestructive throwing-vials in here.  ``

`gSaws, scalpels and other medical and scary-looking instruments lie inneat rows on high counters and bloodied rags lie crumpled on shelves above.The clean smell of embalming fluids spread throughout the room from barrels,barrels containing contorted and dried limbs on morbid display as they hangout from their container, like some kind of monstrous insect.  ``

`gAs the eastern part of this laboratory was neat and organized, thishalf is the opposite.  Pale and stuff c orpses are piled in the corners,their faces frozen in horrible grimaces of terror, curled up in fetalposition or their hands before their faces as if to ward off harm.  ``

`gGranite stones and rubble blocks any further advancement into thetower.  A ferocious fight seems to have taken place here, and the tentacledloser lies partly covered by a cairn of stones that once were the wall ofthe stairwell.  Dust swirls as the tentacles twitch to life...``

Rooms.MaxMsg: There sphere can hold only one creature at a time.
Rooms.RoomDescription: `gFrom inside this sphere, the outside world is nothing but a green blur.The tubes attached to the sphere's outside penetrates the crystal skin ofthe sphere, but the openings of them are lidded.
